{{wikipediapar|Victory over Japan Day}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''VP Day'''
# {{AU}} Victory in the Pacific day, being 15 August 1945, the day after Japanese forces surrendered in [[w:World War II|World War II]].
===Usage note===
This day is known as [[VJ Day]] in other Allied countries, and it is sometimes supposed "VP" is a later substitution, but in Australia VP was the original term.
